The payment schedule of financial instruments defines the dates at which payments are made by one party to another on for example a bond or derivative. It can be either customised or parameterised. The schedule is generated based on a set of rules and market conventions to define the frequencies of the payments. These parameters include: The schedule consists of a series of dates that define exactly when payments will be made. 
